# SSH signing keys recognised by `git verify-commit` for this repo.
# Used by bin/antibody-check and bin/loc-ratchet to turn the `%G?`
# placeholder from N (no-verification-possible) into G / U / E —
# i.e. real signature status codes the gates know how to handle.
#
# Format : <email> <key-type> <key-data> [comment]
# One line per (identity, key) pair. Multiple lines allowed per
# identity for rotation ; list the current AND the previous key
# during a transition.
#
# Authority distinction is enforced in bin/antibody-check based on
# the commit's author email, not the presence of a key here. A key
# in this file gets its signatures VERIFIED ; whether that signature
# authorises an antibody exemption or a loc-ratchet override is a
# separate check (only commits authored by the operator authorise).
# See the header comments in those two scripts for the details.

